# 32-bit
CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=386 go build -ldflags="-s -w" -o core-probe-x86 main.go

# 64-bit
CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -ldflags="-s -w" -o core-probe-x64 main.go


That gives you two binary files. Then on GitHub:

    Go to your repo → Releases → Create a new release
    Tag it — convention is v2.0.0
    Drag and drop both binaries into the release assets
    Publish

Users then download directly from that releases page — which is exactly what the README points them to.

One tip — name the binaries with the version number so users always know what they downloaded:
bash

-o core-probe-v2.0-x86
-o core-probe-v2.0-x64

Keeps releases clean if you ship updates later — no confusion about which binary is which version.
